<P>Mr. Monck Berkeley, one day on his arrival at Cook|ham
from Oxford, &s;itting after dinner, Dr. Berkeley a&s;ked,
<Q REND="inline">"What company he had in the machine to Maidenhead?"</Q>
He replied, <Q REND="inline">"Very &s;en&s;ible, agreeable company."</Q></P>
<P>Dr. B.&mdash;<Q REND="inline">"Probably &s;ome gentlemen of your own ac|quaintance."</Q></P>
<P>Mr. B.&mdash;<Q REND="inline">"No, not one; but I had a very plea&s;ant
drive."</Q></P>
<P>At length, after a &s;hort &s;ilence, Mr. Berkeley &s;aid,
<Q REND="inline">"Well; if ever I marry, and &s;hould have a daughter, I
